""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2068082049672462516", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASswhRFn7", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 874, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "god", "id": 8689109, "raw_content": "", "author": "PiratePatriotParrot", "created": 1781904401123, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Harvestsmiles12", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASswhRFn7.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/i/status/2068082049672462516", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "A few weeks apart in NYC:\r\n\r\n138 year old Astoria church burns\r\n173 year old Bushwick church burns\r\n\r\nThe causes of both fires are not known", "last_comment_created": 1781965972292, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 98, "score_up": 874, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": [{"width": 752, "heightRatio": 106, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HLNNqe2WEAA5mZD.jpg", "height": 799}, {"width": 1080, "heightRatio": 177, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HLNNqejXwAAn--x.jpg", "height": 1920}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 32, "created": 1781904158000, "id": "2068082049672462516", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1563691268793946117/OedvhFeS_normal.jpg", "displayName": "End Wokeness", "username": "EndWokeness"}, "content": "A few weeks apart in NYC:\n\n138 year old Astoria church burns\n173 year old Bushwick church burns\n\nThe causes of both fires are not known", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 146}}, "post_flair_text": "\u271d\ufe0f\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0UNDER GOD\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u271d\ufe0f", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASt1DtlW2", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 13, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8690416, "raw_content": "With girls, virtually all of them are \"I don't need a relationship. I don't need a man to be happy. I'm going to focus on myself.\" And even in relationships, 90% of young women nowadays have, as the expectation is basically \"my career is what's most important to me. Don't you dare take away from my career. My career will always come first and if you can't understand that then that's your problem.\"\n\nMeanwhile, young guys treat nearly everything about relationships besides the sex part like its a burden. They don't want to text their girlfriend, they whine about having to go on dates with her. They complain if their girlfriend is clingy or needy. No one knows how to make girls feel special or valued.\n\nGirls in America are like \"don't you dare take away from my career\" and guys are like \"don't you dare take away from my free time.\" Everyone wants their girlfriend/boyfriend to basically operate like a television set that they press a button to activate whenever they personally feel like activating them. Nobody really values the companionship of the opposite sex anymore or is willing to put any effort into having a relationship with a member of the opposite sex. If they have a girlfriend or boyfriend and lose them, they treat it like they lost a car, and start talking about how the can be replaced right away. Everyone is just a utility to everybody these days...\n\nThis is why so many people are unmarried now.", "author": "MAGA9428", "created": 1781986634117, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Porkbut", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Why is almost nobody romantic anymore?", "last_comment_created": 1781990126249, "content": "<p>With girls, virtually all of them are &quot;I don't need a relationship. I don't need a man to be happy. I'm going to focus on myself.&quot; And even in relationships, 90% of young women nowadays have, as the expectation is basically &quot;my career is what's most important to me. Don't you dare take away from my career. My career will always come first and if you can't understand that then that's your problem.&quot;</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, young guys treat nearly everything about relationships besides the sex part like its a burden. They don't want to text their girlfriend, they whine about having to go on dates with her. They complain if their girlfriend is clingy or needy. No one knows how to make girls feel special or valued.</p>\n<p>Girls in America are like &quot;don't you dare take away from my career&quot; and guys are like &quot;don't you dare take away from my free time.&quot; Everyone wants their girlfriend/boyfriend to basically operate like a television set that they press a button to activate whenever they personally feel like activating them. Nobody really values the companionship of the opposite sex anymore or is willing to put any effort into having a relationship with a member of the opposite sex. If they have a girlfriend or boyfriend and lose them, they treat it like they lost a car, and start talking about how the can be replaced right away. Everyone is just a utility to everybody these days...</p>\n<p>This is why so many people are unmarried now.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 5, "score_up": 13, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}